reviewText:
"The Importance Of Being Earnest"  Great comedy, just love it, this is the 2002 version with the following cast: Rupert Everett As Algernon 'Algy' Moncrieff; Colin Firth As John 'Jack' Worthing; Frances O'Connor As Gwendolen Fairfax; Reese Witherspoon As Cecily Cardew; Judi Dench As Lady Augusta Bracknell; Tom Wilkinson As Dr. Frederick Chasuble; Anna Massey As Miss Laetitia Prism; Edward Fox As Lane, Algy's Butler; Patrick Godfrey As Merriman;
Charles Kay As Gribsby; Cyril Shaps As Pew Opener; Marsha Fitzalan As Dowager; Finty Williams As Young Augusta Bracknell;
Guy Bensley As Young Lord Bracknell; Christina Robert As Duchess of Devonshire; Kiera Chaplin As Girl in Gambling Club;
Alexandra Kobi As Girl in Gambling Club; Suzie Boyle As Dancer; Kate Coyne As Dancer; Bernadette Iglich As Dancer; Polli Redston As Dancer;
Elaine Tyler-Hall As Dancer; Gillian Winn As Dancer; Holly Collins As Dancer; Kit Dickinson As Dancer; Suzanne Thomas As Dancer;
Charlie Mole As Musical Butler; Darrell Kok As Musical Butler; Judd Procter As Musical Butler; Martin Knowles As Musical Butler;
Sacha Bennett As Jenkins the Gamekeeper (uncredited); Ray Donn As Gambler (uncredited); Neil Findlater As Tricycle Man (uncredited);
Sonja Morgenstern As Lady at the Savoy (uncredited)
